content.description: Start left on a slopey dish and right on a decent three finger pocket, both about chest height. Climb straight up through thin holds to better holds and hope you cleaned more moss off the topout than I did.
content.location: Uphill and slightly left of the large turtley boulder. There is a faint old logging road just uphill of the turtle boulder. Beyond that and just inside the tree-line stands this boulder.

content.description: Sit start on the west arete(left), left hand on a great solid crimp, right hand low on the corner, a few powerful moves with fun compression, side pulls and heel hooks to gain the slab, simple top out.Would be a great problem if the steep section lasted a little longer.
content.location: Left of Stuart Little, sit start under the west arete on the Parmesan Boulder.

content.description: Just behind and left of the turtle, this boulder is hidden just inside the tree line.
